title._content: ["Wellsbridge Cottage," Philip Herbert Martineau house, Wellsbridge (near Ascot), England. (LOC)

description._content: Johnston, Frances Benjamin,, 1864-1952,, photographer. ["Wellsbridge Cottage," Philip Herbert Martineau house, Wellsbridge (near Ascot), England. Entrance walk] [1925 August] 1 photograph : glass lantern slide, hand-colored ; 3.25 x 4 in. Notes: Site History. Landscape: Alice Vaughan-Williams [Mrs. Philip] Martineau, from ca. 1920. Title, date, and subject information provided by Sam Watters, 2011. Slide manufactured by Edward Van Altena, 71-79 W. 45th St., New York, N.Y. Forms part of: Garden and historic house lecture series in the Frances Benjamin Johnston Collection (Library of Congress). Published in Gardens for a Beautiful America / Sam Watters. New York: Acanthus Press, 2012. Plate 213. Rights Info: No known restrictions on publication. Repository: Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division, Washington, D.C. 20540 USA, hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.print Higher resolution image is available (Persistent URL): hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/ppmsca.16202 Call Number: LC-J717-X99- 44
